  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Moment of Forces and Couples"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Determine the moment of a given force about a pivot point (see ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Turning-Effect-of-Forces#Moment-of-a-Force",
                      "isActive" : true,
                      "type" : "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ").",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Determine the sign convention of the moment vector.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Combine the moments of several forces to find the resultant moment.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Identify the moments of couples and combine them with the moments of forces.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Sign-Convention",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Sign Convention",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Moments in 2d are either clockwise or counterclockwise. A clockwise moment would be negative",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "from an anticlockwise frame of reference, and vice versa.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The default frame of reference is anticlockwise, so ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "clockwise moments are negative",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It is a good idea to just draw a little ↺ or ↻ on the vector to indicate the direction of rotation.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Combining-Moments",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Combining Moments",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Choose a frame of reference: clockwise or counterclockwise.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Determine the moment of each force about the pivot point, and whether it is clockwise or counterclockwise.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Assign the signs to the moments based on the chosen frame of reference.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Add the moments together to find the resultant moment.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Varignons-Theorem",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Varignon’s Theorem",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you consider a force acting on the end of some complex shape, it may be difficult to determine",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the perpendicular distance between the line of action of the force and the pivot, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$d\\perp$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Diagram_Varignons Theorem",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In such cases, you can use Varignon’s Theorem. To apply it, you need to:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Resolve the force into its x and y components.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Find the resultant moment created by these resolved forces",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "As forces can be resolved into their components, a moment can be resolved into its components as well.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The coordinate systems you should use are ones which align with the information you have available about",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the object, such as in the diagram above.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the diagram above, you can apply the sum of moments as you normally would:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "M_{R} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} F_{i} \\cdot d_{i}",
            "= +(F_{x} \\cdot d_{x}) + (F_y \\cdot d_{y})"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the example above, both components are positive as they align with our chosen frame of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "reference (anticlockwise).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Moments-of-Couples",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Moments of Couples",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A couple (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\tau$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") is a pair of equal and opposite forces acting on an object, separated by a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "distance ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$d\\perp$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The equation to calculate the moment of a couple is:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\tau = F \\cdot d\\perp"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Where:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$\\tau$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the moment of the couple",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$F$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the magnitude of one of the forces",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$d\\perp$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the perpendicular distance between the lines of action of the forces",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The special property of couples is that the moment they create is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "independent",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " of the pivot",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "point. This means that the moment around ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "any point",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the plane of the couple (ie, in 2d) is the same.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Proof-of-Pivot-Agnosticity",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Proof of Pivot Agnosticity",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "(In English: Proof that the moment of a couple is independent of where the pivot point is)",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Consider a stick with points A and B, which are distance ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$d$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " apart. On point A, there is a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "downward force ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$F$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and on point B, there is an upward force ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$F$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". There is also point X,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "which is a distance ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$x$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " from point A.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To calculate the moment of the couple about point X, we can sum the moments of the two forces:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "M_{X} = F \\cdot (d_{A} + x) - F \\cdot (x)",
            "= F \\cdot d_{A} + F \\cdot x - F \\cdot x",
            "= F \\cdot d_{A} = \\tau"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note that because the forces act in opposite directions, we can cancel out the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$x$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " terms, making",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the moment of the couple independent of the pivot point.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
